  "prompt": "Which is the best plan for international calling in India for people in UAE?",
  "response": "There are several plans available for international calling in India for people in the UAE. The best plan might depend on specific factors such as call duration, frequency, and budget. However, some popular and generally well-regarded options include:\n\n1. **VoIP Services**: Applications like Skype, WhatsApp, and Viber are cost-effective for international calling and may offer free or very low-cost calls over the internet.\n\n2. **Local Telecom Providers**: Indian telecom companies such as Jio, Airtel, and Vi offer international calling packs. These packs often come with specific benefits for calls to the UAE. Check their websites or customer service for the most current offers and rates.\n\nListed below are noteworthy plans from major providers:\n   - **Jio**: Offers international calling plans with various validity periods and inclusive minutes for calls to the UAE.\n   - **Airtel**: Provides ISD packs with competitive rates for UAE calling.\n   - **Vi (Vodafone Idea)**: Also offers different ISD packs that include calls to the UAE.\n\n3. **UAE Telecom Providers**: Du and Etisalat offer international calling plans tailored for their subscribers for calling abroad, including to India. Consider checking their offerings for any special packs or promotions.\n\n4. **Calling Cards**: International calling cards can be a good option for those who prefer a pay-as-you-go model. Many online services offer calling cards at competitive rates.\n\n5. **Google Voice**: If available, Google Voice offers competitive rates for international calling.\n\nIt's essential to compare the rates, validity, and additional benefits across these providers and choose the one that best fits your requirements.",
